description: This notification is generated by a UCS node whenever a fault
is active and the fault state changes.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultActiveNotif CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultDescription s EXAMPLE CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultAffectedObjectId o 1.3.6.1.4.1.8072.2.1.1 CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultAffectedObjectDn s EXAMPLE CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultCreationTime s EXAMPLES CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultLastModificationTime s EXAMPLES CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultCode i 156 CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultType i 1 CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultProbableCause i 3 CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultSeverity i 0 CISCO-UNIFIED-COMPUTING-MIB::cucsFaultOccur c 9999
